doc.after: The Xbox 360 launched with 14 games in North America and 13 in Europe. The console's best-selling game for 2005, Call of Duty 2, sold over a million copies.[105] Five other games sold over a million copies in the console's first year on the market: Ghost Recon Advanced Warfighter,[106] The Elder Scrolls IV: Oblivion,[107] Dead or Alive 4,[108] Saints Row,[109] and Gears of War.[110] Gears of War would become the best-selling game on the console with 3 million copies in 2006,[111] before being surpassed in 2007 by Halo 3 with over 8 million copies.[112]
